
SOLUTION

1.fill up 3 -> 3 full, 5 empty
2.pour all from 3 to 5 -> 3 empty, 5 has 3
3.fill up 3 -> 3 full, 5 has 3
4.pour 3 to 5 until 5 is full -> 3 has 1, 5 full
5.pour 5 to somehere -> 3 has 1, 5 empty
6.pour everything from 3 to 5 -> 3 empty, 5 has 1
7.fill up 3 -> 3 full, 5 has 1
8.pour all from 3 to 5 -> 3 empty, 5 has 4
